Install Snort
Command:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install snort -y
Sample Output:
Setting up snort (2.9.x) ...
Snort successfully installed

Verify Snort Installation
Command:
snort --version

Configure Snort
Command:
sudo nano /etc/snort/snort.conf
Configuration Entry:
ipvar HOME_NET 192.168.1.0/24
Sample Output:
Configuration file updated successfully

Test Snort Configuration
Command:
sudo snort -T -c /etc/snort/snort.conf
Sample Output:
Snort successfully validated the configuration!
Run Snort in Intrusion  Detection System Mode
Command:
sudo snort -A console -q -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0
Sample Output:
Running in IDS mode...


Create a Custom  IDS  Rule
Command:
sudo nano /etc/snort/rules/local.rules
Rule Added:
alert icmp any any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ICMP Ping Detected"; sid:1000001; rev:1;)
Sample Output:
Rule saved successfully


Generate Network Traffic
(Open new terminal)
Command:
ping 8.8.8.8
Sample Output:
64 bytes from 8.8.8.8: icmp_seq=1 ttl=117 time=20 ms

Observe IDS Alert
Snort Output:
[**] [1:1000001:1] ICMP Ping Detected [**]

View Snort Log Files
Command:
sudo cat /var/log/snort/alert
Sample Output:
[**] [1:1000001:1] ICMP Ping Detected [**]
